{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.28",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 28 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:1",
      "text": "He who takes vengeance will find vengeance from the Lord, and he will surely make his sins firm.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:2",
      "text": "Forgive your neighbor the hurt that he has done, and then your sins will be pardoned when you pray.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:3",
      "text": "Does anyone harbor anger against another and expect healing from the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:4",
      "text": "Upon a man like himself he has no mercy, and does he make supplication for his own sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:5",
      "text": "He himself, being flesh, nourishes wrath. Who will make atonement for his sins?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:6",
      "text": "Remember your last end, and stop enmity. Remember corruption and death, and be true to the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:7",
      "text": "Remember the commandments, and don’t be angry with your neighbor. Remember the covenant of the Highest, and overlook ignorance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:8",
      "text": "Abstain from strife, and you will diminish your sins, for a passionate man will kindle strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:9",
      "text": "A man who is a sinner will trouble friends and sow discord among those who are at peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:10",
      "text": "As is the fuel of the fire, so it will burn; and as the stoutness of the strife is, so it will burn. As is the strength of the man, so will be his wrath; and as is his wealth, so he will exalt his anger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:11",
      "text": "A contention begun in haste kindles a fire; and hasty fighting sheds blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:12",
      "text": "If you blow on a spark, it will burn; and if you spit upon it, it will be quenched. Both of these come out of your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:13",
      "text": "Curse the whisperer and double-tongued, for he has destroyed many who were at peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:14",
      "text": "A slanderer has shaken many, and dispersed them from nation to nation. It has pulled down strong cities and overthrown the houses of great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:15",
      "text": "A slanderer has cast out brave women and deprived them of their labors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:16",
      "text": "He who listens to it will not find rest, nor will he live quietly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:17",
      "text": "The stroke of a whip makes a mark in the flesh, but the stroke of a tongue will break bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:18",
      "text": "Many have fallen by the edge of the sword, yet not so many as those who have fallen because of the tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:19",
      "text": "Happy is he who is sheltered from it, who has not passed through its wrath, who has not drawn its yoke, and has not been bound with its bands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:20",
      "text": "For its yoke is a yoke of iron, and its bands are bands of brass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:21",
      "text": "Its death is an evil death, and Hades is better than it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:22",
      "text": "It will not have rule over godly men. They will not be burned in its flame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:23",
      "text": "Those who forsake the Lord will fall into it. It will burn among them, and won’t be quenched. It will be sent against them like a lion. It will destroy them like a leopard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:24",
      "text": "As you hedge your possession about with thorns, and secure your silver and your gold,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:25",
      "text": "so make a balance and a weight for your words, and make a door and a bar for your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.28.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 28:26",
      "text": "Take heed lest you slip with it, lest you fall before one who lies in wait.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
